{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Manage macOS virtual machines as Kubernetes resources using the MacOSVM custom resource definition."}],"topicSections":[{"title":"Related Guides","anchor":"Related-Guides","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/GettingStarted","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/GitHubActionsGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/JenkinsGuide"]},{"title":"Key Types","anchor":"Key-Types","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/VirtualMachineSpecification","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/ProvisioningMode"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"Overview","type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The Spooktacular Kubernetes operator lets you manage macOS VMs"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"declaratively with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"kubectl"},{"type":"text","text":". The Swift controller watches"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"MacOSVM"},{"type":"text","text":" custom resources and reconciles them by calling the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Spooktacular HTTP API on your Mac nodes."}]},{"level":3,"anchor":"Architecture","type":"heading","text":"Architecture"},{"syntax":null,"type":"codeListing","code":["┌────────────────────────────────────────────┐","│  Kubernetes Cluster (Linux)                │","│                                            │","│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────┐  │","│  │  spook-controller (Deployment)       │  │","│  │  Watches MacOSVM CRDs               │  │","│  │  Calls HTTP API on Mac nodes        │  │","│  └──────────┬──────────────┬────────────┘  │","└─────────────│──────────────│───────────────┘","              │ HTTP :8484   │ HTTP :8484","   